        "title": "Relative paths in XSL include when called from a JAR",
        "body": "<p>I have an issue that works something like this:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>I have a JAR file in one location that creates HTML using XSL and style sheets.<\/li>\n<li>The XSL and style sheets are located in another folder.<\/li>\n<li>The style sheets have a relative include on them.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>My understanding after reading around online, I call the base XSL document, and then everything else should be relative to that base XSL document.<\/p>\n<p>E.g.&lt;xsl:include href=&quot;./TransmissionData.xsl&quot;/&gt;<\/p>\n<p>But it cannot find that file. Am I missing something? I'll include any other information required if you need more details.<\/p>\n",
